div.p:
All who ſhed teares are not ſtrait way Penitents;
                  Pet. Martyr. loc com. claſ 10. ca. 10. Jer. 15.18. Addidit & lachrymas tanquā mandaſſet & illas, Ovid Metam. l 6. Lachryma nibil citius areſcit, Eraſm. Adag. the hardeſt Marble againſt ſome weather may weepe. And how often do we ſee the Dew to ſtand on the blasted Corne or Graſſe: There are Eying waters ſpoken of by Ieremiah, as well as Clouds without Water ſpoken of by S. Iude. It is an eaſie matter to give you inſtances. Gen. 27.3, 4. 1 Sam. 24.17. Mala. 2.13. Teares are deceitfull things, nothing ſooner dryed up that a Teare, and therfore not to be truſted too far:

For a man may as well go to his Graves-end by water as by Land.

div.head:
And wiped them with the haires of her head. 
                     Text. 
